        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          @vincentpower- By your reasoning, nothing is "undeserved" in football also yet Atletico scored the winner in the first leg via an incorrectly awarded penalty decision. How, by pure definition of the word is that NOT undeserved? If something can be "undeserved" (such as a goal being scored from an incorrectly awarded penalty) then something can be deserved- although when using it to describe the overall run of play and not a single black and white instance, it can be tricky since people will never agree. One could argue that if team A has over 3 times the number of shots and double the number of shots on target as team B then team A deserves to win based on the definition of the word 'deserved'. You clearly don't but I can give you another black and white example where not only is 'deserved' a valid term but it is the definitive one? This may or may not involve human variables.
